title: $:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/changelog
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.0.24 |2026-05-21 |''Preview pane no longer shrinks the result list.'' Previously, opening the details drawer capped `.rcp-results` at 25vh ‚ÄĒ rows that were visible before pressing Ctrl-hold suddenly disappeared, which felt like the preview was overlapping the list. Now `.rcp-preview` is `flex: 0 0 auto` with `max-height: 30vh` and its existing internal scroll ‚ÄĒ the slot claims its content height up to 30vh without stealing space from results. The popup ceiling grows from 60vh ‚Üí 90vh while previewing so the new slot appends ''below'' the result list. If preview body exceeds 30vh the slot scrolls in itself rather than pushing rows out of view. Pure CSS change ‚ÄĒ no restart required. |
|0.0.23 |2026-05-21 |''Pick-and-return leaves + bound drill rows + multi-prefix filter fix.'' (a) New leaf field ''`ca-after-fire`'' ‚ÄĒ default `close` (existing behaviour); `pop` fires the action, pops one stage, and keeps the palette open. Lets single-select sub-drills (ref/enum pickers in a multi-field edit flow) hand the user back to the parent field stage with the pick applied. (b) When a ''`drill`'' row carries `ca-bind-tiddler` + `ca-bind-field`, the palette now renders the currently-bound value on the right of the row ‚ÄĒ references resolved via the target tiddler's `caption` field, multi-select string-array binds comma-joined, empty ‚Üí `(unset)`. Mirrors text/number/date row semantics. (c) ''Direct-Enter on entity instance'' (Find-entity / find-by-kind paths) now sets `parent-picked` = picked.title before firing the entity's default action, matching the convention used inside the action menu. Authored `ca-actions` using `<<parent-picked>>` now work regardless of which path reached the entity. (d) ''Filter-prefix fix'': `makeFakeWidget` delegates to TW core's `Widget.prototype.makeFakeWidgetWithVariables`, which propagates that method onto the returned fake widget. Filter prefixes `:filter`, `:map`, `:reduce`, `:sortsub` call back into it per iteration ‚ÄĒ a hand-rolled stub threw `TypeError`, silently erasing results from any `ca-next-scope` / `ca-items-from` filter using those prefixes. (e) Startup module now wraps the palette in `\import [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/Macro]!has[draft.of]]` so `\function` declarations in `$:/tags/Macro`-tagged tiddlers (kind's `cascade-helpers.tid` etc.) resolve inside the palette's widget scope ‚ÄĒ without this, root-mounted palette couldn't see plugin-supplied filter functions. JS module changed ‚ÄĒ restart required. |
|0.0.22 |2026-05-21 |''Three palette extensions enabling kind integration.'' (a) ''Scribetype-based bind plumbing'' ‚ÄĒ new ''`ca-bind-type`'' field (default `text/plain`) routes read/write of toggle/number/text/date kinds through scribe's scribetype handlers. Backwards-compat preserved. Multi-value editing via ''`ca-bind-type: application/x-string-array`'' makes toggle a list-membership operator (add/remove the trueValue from the bound list). Soft-dep added on ''`$:/plugins/rimir/scribe`''. (b) ''`ca-items-from`'' ‚ÄĒ new drill-item field. A filter returning JSON-encoded item shapes (one per result) populates the inner stage. Lets plugins synthesise stages from configuration data without backing tiddlers. The empty-title items short-circuit override/template/help lookups. Mutually exclusive with ''`ca-next-scope`''. (c) ''`ca-kind: date''' ‚ÄĒ new kind with +/- ¬Īday, Shift ¬Īmonth, Ctrl ¬Īyear (configurable via ''`ca-step-day`'' / ''`ca-step-month`'' / ''`ca-step-year`''). ''Space'' enters typed-edit-mode with the scribetype's smart-parser (ISO / German / today / tomorrow / yesterday / ¬ĪN[d\|w\|m\|y]). Display via ''`ca-date-format`'' (default `DD.MM.YYYY`). Defaults bind-type to `application/x-tw-date` when unset. (d) ''`ca-confirm: yes`'' on a leaf wraps its actions in a confirm-drill instead of firing immediately. ''`ca-confirm-consequence`'' supports `<<picked>>` / `<<parent-picked>>` substitution. Action vars (parent-picked etc.) flow through the confirm stage so the actions resolve identifiers correctly. JS module changed ‚ÄĒ restart required. |
|0.0.21 |2026-05-21 |''v0.2 follow-up fixes.'' (a) Shipped missing config shadow ''`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/max-results`'' (default 30) ‚ÄĒ without it the engine couldn't detect override state, so the ‚óŹ flag never showed and DEL was a no-op on a modified Max results row. (b) ''Always-on'' now reflects live in the UI: details visibility derives from `(ctrlHeld OR always-on)` via a new `_updateDetailsVisibility` helper called from both Ctrl key events AND the wiki change hook when the config flips. (c) New parent-drill field ''`ca-next-as-link: yes`'' suppresses cascade-aware detection of result tiddlers ‚ÄĒ they render as plain link rows (no chevron, Enter navigates) instead of drilling into the entry's own scope. Applied to all three diagnostic drills (Loaded entries / actions / settings) so they behave as inspector lists rather than rabbit holes. |
|0.0.20 |2026-05-21 |''v0.2 ‚ÄĒ three-section focus + detail templates + DEL confirm-drill.'' Major interaction-model refresh: the popup is now three focusable sections (''input | menu | details''), each with its own keyboard branch. ''Tab/Shift-Tab'' cycles focus; in the menu ''‚Üí'' drills, ''‚Üź'' pops; ''Esc'' is context-sensitive (in input ‚Üí close palette entirely; in menu/details ‚Üí return focus to input). ''Ctrl-Enter'' replaces ''Shift-Enter'' for fire+keep-open (Shift-Enter retained as silent alias for back-compat). Details drawer is no longer just a fields-table: new ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/template`'' tag lets plugins ship wikitext templates that render with `currentTiddler` bound to the picked item, with `ca-template-applies` filter for auto-selection and tab strip when multiple templates apply (‚Üź/‚Üí switches tabs). Help text from ''`ca-help`'' (long-form) or ''`ca-hint`'' (fallback) renders as a bold lead-in. New ''Details always on'' setting keeps the drawer visible without holding Ctrl. ''Overridden-default flag:'' rows whose bound config tiddler has both a shadow AND an override get a small ‚óŹ dot; the default value appears in the details drawer. ''DEL/Backspace'' on such rows pushes a confirm-drill (synthetic stage with Confirm/Cancel leaves and a destructive consequence banner in the details). DEL on user-authored tiddlers in diagnostic lists offers the same confirm-drill with a backlink count. New root entry ''Configuration'' aggregates Settings + Diagnostics (replaces their previous root-level placement). Cleanup pass removed dev-only `console.log` boot noise, factored row rendering into per-kind helpers, and grouped constants. JS module changed ‚ÄĒ restart required. |
|0.0.19 |2026-05-20 |''Diagnostics drill + Ctrl-hold preview.'' New root entry ''Diagnostics'' drills into tiddlers tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/diagnostic`'' ‚ÄĒ engine ships three: ''Loaded entries'', ''Loaded actions'', ''Loaded settings'', each a drill listing the corresponding tagged tiddlers. Picking one opens it (fallback `$action-navigate` already covers the no-entity-type case). New gesture: ''hold Ctrl'' to show a fields-table preview drawer of the selected item below the result list. Auto-refreshes on Up/Down (and stage push/pop). Release ‚Üí drawer hides. Suppressed in edit mode (mutually exclusive). The preview surfaces every field, with the `text` body code-block formatted at the bottom for readability ‚ÄĒ useful for inspecting what `ca-next-scope`, `ca-actions`, and friends actually contain on a given entry/action without leaving the palette. |
|0.0.18 |2026-05-20 |''Text kind + edit-mode + hover tooltips + soft-depth setting.'' New ''`ca-kind: text`'' shows the current bound value; ''Space'' pushes the value into the palette's search input (the input switches to a value-editor ‚ÄĒ amber highlight, result list dims) and selects all text for quick replace. ''Enter'' writes back; ''Esc'' discards. Number rows now also accept Space for type-set entry, complementing the +/- nudge gestures. New ''Hotkey'' setting bound to `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open` so users can rebind from inside the palette. Native hover tooltips render `ca-hint` on every row (discoverable help). Refactored ''Soft depth warning'' threshold to read live from `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/soft-depth-warning` (replaces hard-coded constant) and shipped as a number setting (range 3‚Äď30, default 10). |
|0.0.17 |2026-05-20 |''Number kind + slider.'' New ''`ca-kind: number`'' renders a numeric row with an inline horizontal slider bar (when both `ca-min` and `ca-max` are set) and the current value. ''`+`'' / ''`-`'' adjust by `ca-step` (default 1); ''Shift'' uses `ca-step-medium` (default 5); ''Ctrl'' uses `ca-step-large` (default 20). Keys are matched on `e.code` (`Equal`, `NumpadAdd`, `Minus`, `NumpadSubtract`) for layout-portability. Value clamps to [`ca-min`, `ca-max`] on write. Enter closes the palette; Shift-Enter keeps it open. First shipped: ''Max results per stage'' (bound to `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/max-results`, range 5‚Äď100, default 30). |
|0.0.16 |2026-05-20 |''Toggle kind + Settings entry.'' New ''`ca-kind: toggle`'' renders a checkbox row bound to a tiddler/field/JSON-path via scribe-style fields (`ca-bind-tiddler`, `ca-bind-field`, `ca-bind-path`, `ca-true-value`, `ca-false-value`). ''Space'' flips the value inline without closing the palette; Enter flips + closes; Shift-Enter flips + stays. New root entry ''Settings'' drills into all tiddlers tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/setting`'' ‚ÄĒ auto-clustered by contributing plugin so any plugin can ship its own settings without needing a sub-stage. First shipped setting: ''Grouping'' (`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/grouping-enabled`), live-toggleable from the palette. When grouping is off, the engine keeps items in their natural sort and suppresses headers globally. |
|0.0.15 |2026-05-20 |''Visual grouping in result list.'' Items now cluster by contributing plugin: the engine derives a group label from `$tw.wiki.getShadowSource(title)` ‚Üí plugin tiddler's `name` field, so contributors don't need any prefix convention. New optional ''`ca-group`'' field overrides the auto-derived label (use to cross-cluster items from several plugins under a shared header, e.g. "Mutations"). Cluster ordering follows the lowest `ca-order` member of each cluster. Headers are ''suppressed when a stage has only one cluster'' ‚ÄĒ single-plugin action menus still render as flat lists. Applies in both root and drilled stages. `stage.results` is reordered into visual sequence so keyboard arrows still index linearly through visible rows. |
|0.0.14 |2026-05-19 |''Removed appify-specific entries from the engine.'' The ''Switch Apps'' and ''Return to Wiki'' entries previously shipped here were appify-specific contributions and have moved into `rimir/appify` 0.2.29 (under `palette/`). The engine stays domain-agnostic. Catalogue plugins (orga-palette, appify itself, future others) ship entries; the engine just discovers them via the standard tags. |
|0.0.13 |2026-05-19 |''Stale-stage fix.'' When popping a stage (via Esc, Shift-Tab, or breadcrumb click), the now-top stage is recomputed so any state that changed while in deeper stages is reflected. Example: open palette in default wiki ‚Üí Switch Apps ‚Üí Shift-Enter on orga app (palette stays, app activates) ‚Üí Esc back to root ‚Üí Current App entry now appears (visibility filter re-evaluates). |
|0.0.12 |2026-05-19 |''Shift-Enter / Shift-Click fires the action without closing the palette.'' After the action runs, the current stage is recomputed so any field mutations are reflected immediately. Useful for batch ops like "Mark Done on these three tasks" or "Switch sections to compare views" without re-opening the palette each time. Drill items ignore the modifier (drilling doesn't close anyway). Key-hint footer updated. |
|0.0.11 |2026-05-19 |Three changes: (a) ''Critical fix:'' `findActionParent` now prefers the `statewrap` widget over the appify-app widget. `$action-statewrap-navigate` walks `parentWidget` UP looking for the widget whose `statewrapContext` is set ‚ÄĒ and that's the `statewrap` widget itself (a descendant of appify-app, not appify-app). Parenting actions to appify-app meant walking up from there and never visiting statewrap. Symptom: Enter on entries in appify mode did nothing visible (navigate action ran but found no statewrap). Now resolved ‚ÄĒ statewrap navigation works in appify. (b) New engine field ''`ca-visibility-filter`'' on entries: if present and the filter returns empty, the entry is hidden from the root menu. Used by catalogues to gate entries on the active app. (c) Two new demo entries: ''Switch Apps'' (drill to list `$:/tags/rimir/appify/app` tiddlers; picking sets `$:/state/rimir/appify/active-app`) and ''Return to Wiki'' (leaf, visible only when an app is active, clears the active-app state). |
|0.0.10 |2026-05-19 |''Shift-Tab acts as back-out'' (same as Esc ‚ÄĒ pops one stage, closes palette at root). Mentioned as optional in the original keyboard model but wasn't wired; now it is. Key-hint footer updated. |
|0.0.9 |2026-05-19 |Three improvements: (a) action-parent resolution now prefers `appify-app` widget over plain navigator. The action widget inherits appify-app's variable scope (statewrap channels, instance ID) so `$action-statewrap-navigate` and friends actually work inside appify. Falls back to navigator, then rootWidget. Method renamed from `findNavigator` to `findActionParent`. (b) Items returned by a stage's `ca-next-scope` are now inspected for a `ca-kind` field ‚ÄĒ if present, they're treated as cascade-aware entries (drill or leaf) rather than plain dynamic items. Enables hierarchical "entry group" patterns like `Orga types ‚Üí 12 entity-type entries ‚Üí drill into each`. (c) Dynamic item rows now render with a right-aligned dimmed title column (raw tiddler title) and prefer the `caption` field for the left-aligned display name. Title truncates with ellipsis and shows the full title on hover. |
|0.0.8 |2026-05-19 |Two fixes uncovered after the 0.0.7 startup-module mount: (a) navigator-routed actions (`<$action-navigate>`, `tm-edit-tiddler`, etc.) silently failed because the widget now lives in document.body ‚ÄĒ outside the navigator's widget subtree. New `invokeViaNavigator` helper finds the navigator widget under `$tw.pageWidgetNode` at action-fire time and invokes the action wikitext with the navigator as parentWidget so events bubble naturally into its handlers. Falls back to `$tw.rootWidget` if no navigator found (so global messages like `tm-save-wiki` still work). (b) Selected row now calls `scrollIntoView({block: "nearest"})` so it stays visible when navigating past the viewport bounds. |
|0.0.7 |2026-05-19 |Mount moved from `$:/tags/AboveStory` (tiddler-based) to a startup module that injects the widget directly into `document.body`. Reason: `AboveStory` doesn't render inside appify's substituted UI, so the palette silently failed in app mode. Startup-module mount is independent of any template tag ‚ÄĒ the widget DOM is always present regardless of which UI mode is active. Mount tiddler (`mount.tid`) deleted; new file `widgets/cascade-palette-startup.js`. |
|0.0.6 |2026-05-19 |UI visibility fix ‚ÄĒ replaced fragile `<<colour ...>>` macros with hardcoded colors (light baseline + `prefers-color-scheme: dark` override). Selected row now has a blue background, white text, and a darker left-border accent so the highlight is obvious regardless of theme. Earlier symptom: popup looked greyed-out except for the input field, and selected rows only changed text color. |
|0.0.5 |2026-05-19 |Default hotkey reverted to ''Ctrl-Space'' ‚ÄĒ works correctly once the trailing-newline fix (0.0.4) is in place. The earlier "Ctrl-Space doesn't reach TW" symptom was actually the trailing-newline parse failure all along. |
|0.0.4 |2026-05-19 |Shortcut-key tiddler trailing newline fix ‚ÄĒ the shipped `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open` was a `.tid` file ending in `\n`, so TW resolved `((rimir-cascade-palette-open))` to `"ctrl-space\n"` and the parser couldn't match the key. Rewrote without trailing newline and omitted `type` field per `feedback-tid-vs-txt-meta` (avoids `.txt`+`.meta` split on user edits). |
|0.0.3 |2026-05-19 |Mount tag fixed (`$:/tags/AboveStory` instead of `$:/tags/PageTemplate` ‚ÄĒ wrong tag prevented the widget from rendering). Default hotkey changed from `ctrl-space` to `alt+p` ‚ÄĒ Ctrl-Space reaches Chrome JS but TW's keyboard manager doesn't match it on some Windows / WSL Chrome setups. Diagnostic console logs at widget mount + hotkey-listener registration + message receipt; harmless in production. Settings + readme document the rebind path. |
|0.0.2 |2026-05-19 |''Engine v0.1.'' Cascade widget with stage stack, Tab/Esc/Enter keyboard model, entry discovery via `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`, action discovery via `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action` filtered by `ca-entity-type` (plus globals via `ca-entity-type: *`), filter substitution variables `<<query>>` / `<<picked>>` / `<<parent-picked>>` / `<<stage-N-picked>>`, 3-tier default-action resolution (stage default ‚Üí entity default ‚Üí navigate fallback), breadcrumb with click-to-jump-back, four demo entries (Control Panel, Save Wiki, Advanced Search, Recent Tiddlers‚Ä¶). Doc tabs still scaffold-level ‚ÄĒ full protocol doc lands in 0.0.4. |
|0.0.1 |2026-05-19 |''Initial scaffold.'' Plugin skeleton ‚ÄĒ readme, documentation, settings, changelog, license, icon, doc-template overview. No widget yet. |
